    "_postman_id": "cms-error-edge-cases-collection",
    "name": "CMS - Error Handling & Edge Cases",
    "description": "Error Handling and Edge Cases collection for the Clinic Management System with Clean Architecture.\n\n## � Error Handling & Edge Cases Testing\n\nThis collection focuses specifically on error scenarios and edge case testing:\n\n- **Validation Errors**: Test various validation failure scenarios\n- **Authentication Failures**: Invalid tokens, expired sessions, unauthorized access\n- **Not Found Scenarios**: Missing resources, invalid IDs\n- **Conflict Errors**: Duplicate data, business rule violations\n- **Server Errors**: 500 errors, database connection issues\n- **Rate Limiting**: API rate limit testing\n- **Malformed Requests**: Invalid JSON, missing headers, wrong content types\n- **Edge Cases**: Boundary conditions, extreme values, null/empty data\n\n## Testing Coverage\n\n- ✅ Input validation error testing\n- ✅ Authentication and authorization failures\n- ✅ Resource not found scenarios\n- ✅ Data conflict and duplication errors\n- ✅ Server error simulation\n- ✅ Malformed request handling\n- ✅ Boundary condition testing\n- ✅ Rate limiting verification\n- ✅ Error response format validation\n- ✅ Error message clarity and consistency\n\n## Environment Variables\n\nThis collection uses the following environment variables:\n- `cms_local`: http://localhost:4000 (for local development)\n- `cms_prod`: https://capstone-api.up.railway.app (for production)\n- `baseUrl`: Base URL for API endpoints\n- `authToken`: JWT token for authenticated requests\n- Various test data variables for dynamic testing",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": {
      "major": 2,
      "minor": 3,
      "patch": 0
    }
  },
